# Backend Conventions

## LangGraph nodes

Every node has the signature `(state: XxxState) -> partial state` and returns only the keys it modifies.
Wrap heavy work in `with Timer(metrics.node_timings_ms, "node_key"):`.

## Invariants

Add postconditions to `app/invariants.py` via `check()` — never bare `assert`.

## Settings

All config via `app/config.py` (`get_settings()`). No hardcoded paths or API keys.

## Schemas

- `schemas/chat.py` — API request/response types
- `schemas/cv.py` — CV generation domain
- `schemas/rag.py` — chunks, retrieval

## API

- `api/routes/` — routers per resource
- `main.py` — app factory only; mounts routers

## RAG

- `rag/chunker.py` — section-aware splitting
- `rag/store.py` — ChromaDB wrapper
- `rag/retriever.py` — top-k search, score threshold

## Adding a new agent node

1. Implement node in `agents/*.py`
2. Register in `StateGraph` with explicit edges
3. Add invariant checks after critical mutations
4. Add unit test with mocked LLM/embeddings
